metadata.name: Dreamcatcher Forest #85
metadata.description:
"Dreamcatcher Forest" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022. The illustration in this work draws inspiration from Native American dreamcatchers, a protective talisman crafted from beautifully intricate patterns of woven thread, built from natural materials & colorful beads.

Dreamcatchers are used to protect dreamers while they sleep. Good dreams are able to slip through the web to meet the sleeper beneath, while bad dreams are trapped and prevented.

- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "P" key to export a print-quality image.

metadata.name: Halcyon #54
metadata.description:
Halcyon is a companion piece to, or an evolution of my previous piece, Bedlam. Working off the same physics engine, I aimed to create something more expressive, experimenting with new approaches to brushes, and using those new brushes to create new tones from the same palette as Bedlam. I've also removed the limit for the background, so the work can in turn be more colorful, and wont be limited to what can be created on "traditional" canvas colors. The canvas is now 8x10 to allow for easy printing of the piece if you choose to display it on your wall :)

There are three brush styles (Origami, Floral, and Pop), four stroke modes (ranging from meandering to curvy to jagged), two splatter types (triangular or round), and 25 color palettes, which means there are 100 possible background colors.

Press 's' when in live mode to save a .png

metadata.name: Interlaced #221
metadata.description:
From African tribal clothes to Islamic mosaics every civilization throughout history has produced delicate patterns to share the essence of their culture. These artifacts have changed our understanding of how art, like societies form through bonds, the very fabric of things that have become symbols for cycles, paths and relationships.

Interlaced explores these unique motifs using emergent algorithms to produce colorful continuous patterns. The project uses a dynamic engine that traverses triangular meshes placing diverse tile configurations. By combining art with technology, the project aims to tell a new story of making digital connections between geography, culture and time.

Press ‚Äús‚Äù to save in high-resolution.

metadata.name: Scaffold #123
metadata.description:
The thoughts we have are rarely as ordered as the words we speak and the actions we take are shaped by expectation and conditioning.

As we grow up, we are taught to behave or even think in a certain way. We learn what is acceptable and what is not. Our thoughts are forced to align with the structure imposed upon us.

Scaffold is an attempt to visually explore this concept of thoughts and control. Each output represents a state of mind at a particular moment in time.

Palettes have been mostly named by my family based on the first word they thought of when they saw them.

Keyboard commands:

s - save as png
h - toggle high resolution‚Ä®
b - toggle background texture
a - switch aspect ratio
r - new moment

metadata.name: fields #38
metadata.description:
A generative sketchbook of ideas for a sculpture garden.

Fields builds off Stan Allen's seminal essay "Field Conditions" in which he laid out a prototypical theory of architectural field schemes. Field Conditions are opposed to figural or object-based compositional strategies and approach a site from a systemic point of view. These fields contain a range of possible wall-types. Some produce enclosures, while others dictate a wandering path.

Built with p5.js
By office ca
2022
